Here’s something new 😍✨ I’ve been overflowing with peace, and gratitude for a while now. So I figured I’d share a snapshot into my life. Here’s to the first episode 🥂🍷

This will not be a daily series, but an ongoing one. I’m thrilled to unfold and share the sheer beauty of my journey. 🤗🧡🫶🏽

✨✨Something that challenged me today: Its way too cold to wake up early and go for a walk. So I got back in the bed. 

✨✨Something I seek for Tomorrow: I’d like to actually go to the gym.

✨✨Bible study: Deuteronomy 17 - in this chapter… I learned how God prepared Israel for a king upon their request. They didn’t have one before but thrived under God’s law, compared to neighboring nations serving little “g” gods. God gave instructions for their future king, emphasizing the avoidance of false gods. The King was restricted in wives, silver, and gold. Upon taking the throne, the king had to handwrite an approved copy of God’s law, to be kept with him for life, emphasizing its importance. 

I hope you enjoyed this 🤗 if not… I did lol 🫶🏽 much love to you all.
